**Parent Jira:** https://jira2.workday.com/browse/DEVSERVICES-2813

## Overview:

Flowise’s REST API was found to permit any user with access to any objects referenced by ID (e.g. orgId, workspaceId, chatflowId, chatId, datastore keys) without conducting any ownership checks. Users are subject to initial authentication, but thereafter, knowledge of any one of these IDs (all of which are UUIDv4) is sufficient to read or modify the corresponding resources, even if they belong to other tenants.

## Current System:

**Data Model:**

![][image1]

* User can have a role on the Workspace  
* User can have a delivered role on the Organization  
  * Owner  
  * Member  
* Roles are common for the organization.   
* Within an organization, roles are shared across all Workspaces.

### Role:

The user who has “Manage Roles” permission can create, update or delete roles. **![][image2]**  
**![][image3]**

### 

### Workspace:

Users with workspace permissions are able to:

* Create new workspaces  
* Add or remove users from a workspace  
* Update existing user roles within a workspace

![][image4]![][image5]

### API:

Managing REST API access does not involve separate actions within the current permissions system.

**API Authorization:**

API authorization is based on the following mode.

1. **Organization Owner:** Full Access  
2. **~~User with API Key Validated Flag (Logged in user with session):~~** ~~Full Access~~  
3. Logged in User with session: Role based permission for respective workspace  
4. API Key \- Bearer token: Full Access  
5. **Permissions by user Role:** Specific access allowed via User’s role for the workspace

API permission checks are performed based on the routing configuration implemented for each API.

Whitelist URL: What is the purpose of this?  
[https://github.com/FlowiseAI/Flowise/blob/main/packages/server/src/utils/constants.ts](https://github.com/FlowiseAI/Flowise/blob/main/packages/server/src/utils/constants.ts)

Example, Chatflows ([chatflows/index.ts](https://github.com/FlowiseAI/Flowise/blob/main/packages/server/src/routes/chatflows/index.ts))

*// CREATE*  
router.post('/', checkAnyPermission('chatflows:create,chatflows:update'), chatflowsController.saveChatflow)

*// READ*  
router.get('/', checkAnyPermission('chatflows:view,chatflows:update'), chatflowsController.getAllChatflows)  
router.get(\['/', '/:id'\], checkAnyPermission('chatflows:view,chatflows:update,chatflows:delete'), chatflowsController.getChatflowById)  
router.get(\['/apikey/', '/apikey/:apikey'\], chatflowsController.getChatflowByApiKey)

*// UPDATE*  
router.put(\['/', '/:id'\], checkAnyPermission('chatflows:create,chatflows:update'), chatflowsController.updateChatflow)

*// DELETE*  
router.delete(\['/', '/:id'\], checkPermission('chatflows:delete'), chatflowsController.deleteChatflow)

*// CHECK FOR CHANGE*  
router.get('/has-changed/:id/:lastUpdatedDateTime', chatflowsController.checkIfChatflowHasChanged)

**Permission Check:** [PermissionCheck.ts](https://github.com/FlowiseAI/Flowise/blob/main/packages/server/src/enterprise/rbac/PermissionCheck.ts) 

1. Validate Is the user logged in?  
2. When isApiKeyValidated is true, the user is granted access without checking specific permissions,   
3. If user OrganizationOwner then allow  
4. Validate the user permissions
